# Handoff Discipline Rule

## Purpose
Make multi-agent collaboration explicit and low-friction.

## Requirements
- state assumptions, constraints, and unresolved questions
- preserve ownership boundaries
- pass only the context needed for the next agent
- do not silently redefine another agent's contract
- identify upstream and downstream effects when changing interfaces

## Apply When
- routing work between agents
- escalating to architecture
- handing code from one layer to another
- summarizing partial work for continuation
